  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Tuesday. Mom introduced a new system today: we can earn our own pocket money by finishing certain chores around the house.",
      "zh": "星期二。媽媽今天推出一套新制度：我們可以靠完成家裡某些家事，賺自己的零用錢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She taped a chore chart to the fridge, listing each task and exactly how much it is worth.",
      "zh": "她把一張家事表貼在冰箱上，列出每項任務，還有各自值多少錢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This is your duty now,\" she said, handing William a small broom. \"Being responsible for your own space starts young.\"",
      "zh": "「這是你現在的責任了，」她一邊說，一邊把一支小掃把遞給 William：「對自己的空間負責，要從小開始。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "My tasks included folding laundry, feeding Perry, and taking out the trash, none of which sounded glamorous but all of which pay actual money.",
      "zh": "我的任務包括摺衣服、餵 Perry，還有倒垃圾，聽起來都不怎麼光鮮亮麗，但每一項都真的能賺到錢。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's tasks were smaller, matching his age, but he still complained that sweeping the porch was clearly the hardest job in the entire house.",
      "zh": "William 的任務比較小，符合他的年紀，但他還是抱怨掃陽台顯然是整個家裡最辛苦的工作。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of the week, I had earned enough to open my very first savings account at the bank, which felt oddly like becoming an adult overnight.",
      "zh": "到了週末，我已經賺到足夠的錢，可以去銀行開我人生第一個儲蓄帳戶，感覺一夜之間莫名其妙變成了大人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad explained that our family's electricity bill and water bill are much bigger expenses than my little pile of chore money, just to keep things in perspective.",
      "zh": "爸爸解釋，我們家的電費帳單和水費帳單，開銷比我這一小疊零用錢大多了，讓我對事情有個比較清楚的比例概念。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Managing money is not just about how much you earn,\" he said. \"It is about how wisely you manage what you have.\"",
      "zh": "「理財不只是關於你賺多少錢，」他說：「而是關於你多聰明地管理你手上有的東西。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, meanwhile, spent his entire first week's income on a single toy dinosaur and immediately regretted it by dinner time.",
      "zh": "同時，William 把他第一週全部的收入都花在一隻玩具恐龍上，晚餐時間就馬上後悔了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He then tried to borrow money from me, promising to pay it back \"soon,\" a promise I already knew meant he was creating a small debt he had no plan to repay.",
      "zh": "他接著想跟我借錢，答應「很快」就會還，這個承諾我一聽就知道，代表他正在製造一筆他根本沒打算還的小小債務。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I will charge you interest,\" I joked, and he looked at me like I had personally invented a whole new form of injustice.",
      "zh": "「我要跟你收利息，」我開玩笑地說，他看我的眼神，好像我剛親手發明了一種全新的不公不義。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia, listening from the kitchen, said real wealth was never just about cash in an account, but about family, health, and good rice.",
      "zh": "Sophia 在廚房裡聽到了，說真正的財富從來不只是帳戶裡的現金，而是家人、健康，還有好吃的米飯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"When I was young, we were poor by money, but never poor by love,\" she said, in the tone she uses for lessons she considers extremely important.",
      "zh": "「我年輕的時候，我們金錢上很窮，但在愛上從來不窮，」她用她講重要人生課題時特有的語氣說。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I asked her if she would rather be rich now, and she laughed and said riches without people to share them with sound very lonely.",
      "zh": "我問她現在會不會想要有錢，她笑著說，有財富卻沒有人可以分享，聽起來滿孤單的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One of my new tasks each week is delivering the neighbor's newspaper, since her delivery boy moved away last month.",
      "zh": "我每週的新任務之一，是幫鄰居送報紙，因為她原本的送報男孩上個月搬走了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It is a small job, but the neighbor pays fairly, thanks me every single time, and once even gave me a valuable old coin as a bonus.",
      "zh": "這是個小工作，但那位鄰居付得很公道，每次都會謝謝我，還有一次送了我一枚很有價值的古老硬幣當作獎金。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By Sunday, my little savings account had grown just slightly, but I felt strangely proud watching that small number go up.",
      "zh": "到了星期天，我的小小儲蓄帳戶只成長了一點點，但看著那個小小的數字往上升，我莫名地感到驕傲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, still recovering from his dinosaur-related poverty, asked if he could work off his debt by doing my chores for a week.",
      "zh": "William 還在從恐龍造成的貧窮中恢復，問他能不能靠幫我做一週的家事來還債。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I agreed, mostly because watching an eight-year-old take out the trash responsibly felt like a small, valuable victory of its own.",
      "zh": "我同意了，主要是因為看著一個八歲小孩負責任地倒垃圾，本身就感覺是一場小小的、有價值的勝利。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: earning money teaches you a lot, but apparently not as much as watching your little brother learn it the hard way.",
      "zh": "今日心得：賺錢能教會你很多事，但顯然比不上看著自己的弟弟用慘痛的方式學到這一課。"
    }
  ],
